external_knowledge:
- "Man of the match" is an award given to the best performing player in a match;
- "International Test Cricket" is a form of international cricket that involves longer, more strategic matches;
- "Centuries" refer to a player scoring 100 runs in a single innings.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM matches 
WHERE match_type IN ('ODI', 'Test');

external_knowledge:
- A batting average above 40 is considered very good in cricket, indicating a high level of skill and consistency.;
- One-Day Internationals (ODIs) are a form of limited-overs cricket played between two teams with each team facing a maximum of 50 overs.;
- Playing more than 50 matches in ODIs is a significant milestone, suggesting a player has had a long and successful career in this format.

- "Top-performing team" refers to the team that meets the criteria of playing more than 10 matches, winning more than 5, and having players who collectively score more than 1000 runs or take more than 50 wickets, with at least 5 such players;
- "Played more than 10 matches" and "won over 5" are specific performance metrics for the team;
- "Collectively scored more than 1000 runs or taken more than 50 wickets" refers to the combined performance of the team's players.

- 'Role' '1' refers to players who are both batsmen and bowlers (all-rounders);
- Batting average is calculated as the total runs scored divided by the number of times the player has been out;
- Economy rate is calculated as the number of runs conceded divided by the number of overs bowled.

- 'Active batsmen' refers to players whose current status is 'active' and whose role is 'batsman';
- 'Top' refers to the players with the highest runs scored;
- 'More than 10 matches' means the player has played over 10 matches.

- "ensemble of players" refers to the number of players in each team;
- "star performers wielding the bat with the greatest finesse" refers to the top batsmen based on batting average;
- "top batsmen" are determined by the highest batting average within each team.

- "Average performance" refers to the combination of average runs and average wickets;
- "Top-performing player" is determined by the highest average runs, and in case of a tie, the highest average wickets;
- "Runs" are the total runs scored by a player in cricket;
- "Wickets" are the number of players dismissed by a bowler.

